types.section:
{{fr-noun|f|mesdames}}

# {{ng|a title or form of address for a woman, formerly for a married woman and now commonly for any adult woman regardless of marital status, used both in direct and third-person address}}
#: {{ux|fr|Bonjour, '''madame''', comment puis-je vous aider ?|Hello, '''ma'am''', how can I help you?}}
#: {{ux|fr|Si vous êtes libre, pourriez-vous aider '''madame''', s'il vous plaît?|If you're free, could you help '''this lady''', please?}}
# [[madam]], [[Mrs.]] or [[Ms.]]; {{ng|a title used with a woman's full name or surname, or (in childish language) her first name}}
# {{lb|fr|in children's language|childish}} [[lady]], woman
#: {{ux|fr|Dis merci à la '''madame.'''|Say thank you to the '''lady.'''}}
# the female employer of a domestic servant
#* {{quote-journal|fr|author=Laure Stéphan|title=« Ma Madame m’a dit qu’ils ne pouvaient plus me payer » : au Liban, le calvaire des domestiques éthiopiennes|url=https://www.lemonde.fr/international/article/2020/06/29/dans-le-liban-en-pleine-crise-economique-le-calvaire-des-domestiques-ethiopiennes_6044595_3210.html|journal=Le Monde|year=2020|text=Mazaa, 23 ans, ancienne nourrice et femme de ménage, croix autour du cou, cache son visage. « Ma '''Madame''' (employeuse) m’a dit qu’ils ne pouvaient plus me payer.{{nb...}} »|t=Mazaa, 23 years old, former nanny and housekeeper, a cross around her neck, hides her face. "My '''''madame''''' (employer) told me they couldn't pay me anymore.{{nb...}}"}}

====Usage notes====
*Unlike in English, ''Madame'' is frequently used without a name or article as a polite reference to a woman in the third person, notably in official registers:
*: {{ux|fr|'''Madame''' s'est présentée à l'urgence à 18 h 12.|t='''The/This lady/The patient/Ms. [name]''' attended the emergency room at 6:12 p.m.}}

*Although ''un/le monsieur'' is used as a common noun to mean "a/the gentleman," using the word ''une/la madame'' to mean "a/the lady" is considered childish language. Instead, ''une/la {{m|fr|dame}}'' is used.

